&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pre-Assessment Staff Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time 37.5 hours &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bournemouth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest healthcare charity. We’re balancing our social values with strong business discipline to help the UK get healthy and stay that way. We’re all about great people, too – recruiting and nurturing talent in a supportive, development-led setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Right now, we’re looking for an Pre-Assessment Staff Nurse to join our team in Bournemouth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 1957, Nuffield Hospital Bournemouth is an exceptionally caring environment with 41 beds, 3 Theatres, an Endoscopy room, a Cardiac Catheter Suite and 2 Outpatient Theatres (minor procedures). Our service provision is varied, covering everything from Outpatients and minor procedures through to major surgical specialties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced Staff Nurse who is currently NMC registered and who has experience working in a Pre-Assessment Department setting. Candidates should have experience in carrying out phlebotomy, baseline measurements, ECG, MRSA screening etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent English language skills, IT literacy and the ability to comply with NMC standards for record keeping is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours and Shifts&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They must be available to work a variety of shifts throughout the week. Shift pattern – mixture of early, late and mid shifts of 10am to 6pm or similar Monday to Saturday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although this is a full time post we are happy to consider applications from people looking for part time hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Any applicants wishing to visit the department prior to applying or interview would be welcome to make contact. This position may close early if we find the right candidate.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we offer a working environment that will help you grow your skills and experience and get the best out of life. Other benefits include 25 days’ annual holiday (increasing with service), gym membership, private healthcare and a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - Up to £30,000 per annum (Dependant on Experience)&lt;br /&gt;Location - Bournemouth&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type - Permanent&lt;br /&gt;Full Time, 37.5 hours &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
